    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 MODEL - LIGHT SYSTEMS - TROUBLESHOOTING - Daytime Running
        Lights (DRL) - Canada
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Daytime Running Lights (DRL) - Canada</title>
        <table id="t0828011" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Daytime Running Lights (DRL) - Canada</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.55in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.74in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.82in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.74in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.76in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.48in"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES - IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO - OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Move key switch to accessories position and at 10A fuse F10-A and circuit 12R, measure
                                voltage to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>F10-A, 12R to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 12R from A3 accessories adapter (593),
                                then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Remove DRL day relay (475), move key sw. to accessories position, and at circuit 66A,
                                measure voltage to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(475), 66A to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in 10A fuse F10-A or circuit 66A, then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>At relay socket (475), measure voltage from circuit 66A to 66-GA.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(475), 66A to 66-GA.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 66-GA or G6 gnd. adapter, then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>At relay socket (475), measure voltage from circuit 66B to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(475), 66B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 66B, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Remove DRL night relay (474), move headlight switch to on position, and measure
                                voltage from circuit 66H to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(474), 66H to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 66H from headlight relay (462-R4), then
                                repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>With headlight switch on, at relay socket (474), measure voltage from circuit 66H to
                                66-GB.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>(474), 66H to 66-GB.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 66-GB, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>With headlight switch still on, at (474), measure voltage from circuit 66H to 66-GC.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(474), 66H to 66-GC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 66-GC, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Disconnect park brake switch connector (293), and with parking brakes applied, measure
                                resistance across switch.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Across sw. (293).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>> 100K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace defective switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>With wheels chocked, release parking brakes and measure resistance across switch
                                (293).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Across sw. (293).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>&#60; 1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace defective switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>With wheels still chocked and parking brake still released, reconnect conn. (293).
                                Measure resistance from relay socket (474) circuit 66E to relay socket (475) circuit
                                66D.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(474), 66E to (475), 66D.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>&#60; 1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 66E or 66D, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>11.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Bench test DRL night relay (474) by measuring resistance from terminal 30 to 87A.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Relay (474), term. 30 to 87A.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>&#60; 1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace defective DRL relay.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>12.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Bench test DRL night relay (474) by applying +12 volts to terminal 86, ground to
                                terminal 85, and measuring resistance from terminal 30 to 87.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Energized relay (474), term. 30 to 87.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>&#60; 1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace defective DRL relay.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>13.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Bench test DRL day relay (475) by measuring resistance from terminal 30 to 87A.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Relay (475), term. 30 to 87A.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>&#60; 1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace defective DRL relay.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>14.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Bench test DRL day relay (475) by applying +12 volts to terminal 86, ground to
                                terminal 85, and measuring resistance from terminal 30 to 87.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Energized relay (475), term. 30 to 87.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>&#60; 1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace defective DRL relay.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>15.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Disconnect connector (490) going to headlights, and with park brake applied, measure
                                resistance from circuit 66J to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(490), 66J to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>&#60; 1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>DRL circuits check good.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 66J going to DRL day relay (475), then
                                repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
